ition-colors">Insights</p></a><a href="../contact"><p class="text-current font-body text-xl leading-none hover:text-yellow transition-colors">Contact</p></a></div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit col-span-full pb-8 border-l border-current pl-unit pt-unit h-full"><div class="col-span-6 pr-6"><p class="text-current font-body text-xl">Bolt Builds is a design, build, and fabrication firm located in Greenpoint, Brooklyn.</p><div class="pt-4"><a class="block hover:text-yellow transition-colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=202+Banker+Street+Brooklyn+NY+11222"><p class="text-current font-body text-xl">202 Banker Street</p><p class="text-current font-body text-xl">Brooklyn, NY 11222</p></a><a class="text-current font-body text-xl block hover:text-yellow transition-colors" href="mailto:hello@bolt.build">hello@bolt.build</a><a class="text-current font-body text-xl block hover:text-yellow transition-colors" href="tel:+1 917-740-3463">+1 917-740-3463</a></div></div></div></div><div class="col-span-2 lg:col-span-1 border-t-0 lg:border-t border-x md:border-x-0 border-current"></div></div></div><div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10"><div class="cover-image-shim absolute inset-0 z-10"></div><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Fd6226efb5579f86fc5b5892fc8d870e080f4b417-1080x1350.png&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Fd6226efb5579f86fc5b5892fc8d870e080f4b417-1080x1350.png&w=1080&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Fd6226efb5579f86fc5b5892fc8d870e080f4b417-1080x1350.png&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="" width="1080" height="1350" class="absolute object-cover w-full h-full z-0 inset-0" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 300vw, (max-width: 1000px) 200vw, 100vw"/></div><div class="border-x flex-1 flex flex-col justify-end"></div></header><div class="z-20 relative bg-white"><div class="sticky top-0 invisible"><div class="px-unit absolute left-0 right-0 bg-white"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-b"></div></div></div><div class="px-unit"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-x"><div class="sticky top-unit"><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-2 pb-4"><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-3 pr-2"><p class="text-current font-body text-3xl">Matter of Design | Glass Blocks</p></div><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-2"><h3 class="text-current font-body text-md">November 18, 2025</h3></div></div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-8 pb-unit"><div class="col-start-1 col-end-13 md:col-start-2 md:col-end-12 lg:col-start-4 lg:col-end-12 xl:col-start-4 xl:col-end-10"><p class="text-current font-body text-xl mt-12 first:mt-0 mb-4 font-medium">Glass Blocks</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><br/>From raw origins to refined forms, we spotlight the materials that shape how we build, live, and experience spaces.</p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F41e31ff5c811c3d973adf829047f5aad654c29e4-1080x1350.png&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F41e31ff5c811c3d973adf829047f5aad654c29e4-1080x1350.png&w=1080&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F41e31ff5c811c3d973adf829047f5aad654c29e4-1080x1350.png&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="telo labs glass blocks" width="1080" height="1350" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Glass block, made by melting silica sand, ash stone, and limestone into hollow forms, varies in color, size, and texture. It balances opacity and transparency, diffusing light and defining spatial rhythm with a sculptural, timeless presence.</p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F9192a12b5ab04988d37faa6d059b510807fe86e8-2048x1536.png&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F9192a12b5ab04988d37faa6d059b510807fe86e8-2048x1536.png&w=2048&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F9192a12b5ab04988d37faa6d059b510807fe86e8-2048x1536.png&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="lumea glass blocks" width="2048" height="1536" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">In Reflect Architecture’s project for Lumea, a sweeping glass block wall anchors the entrance of the space. Diffusing light, softening acoustics, and adding a sculptural, timeless presence to the interior. Its gentle curve and translucent texture create a luminous backdrop that balances privacy with openness.<br/></p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F9b444a1e9df6f3b1bbbe6aef95fe10fd3a3c83ce-1536x2048.png&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F9b444a1e9df6f3b1bbbe6aef95fe10fd3a3c83ce-1536x2048.png&w=1920&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F9b444a1e9df6f3b1bbbe6aef95fe10fd3a3c83ce-1536x2048.png&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="lumea glass blocks" width="1536" height="2048" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Fd72220967ff7ad6c96b71cb5fab8158bc7c6108a-1600x1261.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Fd72220967ff7ad6c96b71cb5fab8158bc7c6108a-1600x1261.jpg&w=1920&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Fd72220967ff7ad6c96b71cb5fab8158bc7c6108a-1600x1261.jpg&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt=" Maison Hermès glass blocks" width="1600" height="1261" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">In Renzo Piano Building Workshop’s design for Maison Hermès in Tokyo, a luminous facade of glass blocks shapes the building’s distinctive character. The gridded surface captures and diffuses light, transforming the structure into a glowing beacon within the city. This material lends both structural precision and an ethereal sense of openness.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Faa0023a5362cdc04e959cb92f9c6c0620e4891a8-762x971.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Faa0023a5362cdc04e959cb92f9c6c0620e4891a8-762x971.jpg&w=828&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2Faa0023a5362cdc04e959cb92f9c6c0620e4891a8-762x971.jpg&w=1920&q=75;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x" alt="Maison Hermès glass blocks" width="762" height="971" loading="lazy"/></div><div class="mt-16"><div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center pt-6 pb-8"><div><p class="text-current font-body text-xl text-black mx-auto text-center max-w-[420px]">Subscribe to our newsletter to get the latest updates, insights, and articles from our team.</p><div class="mt-4 text-center"><div class="border-black borde